# Vendure Backend Plugin Development Rules

This project is a Vendure v3.5+ e-commerce backend using TypeScript, NestJS, TypeORM, PostgreSQL, and GraphQL. All custom features are implemented as self-contained plugins in `src/plugins/`.

## Plugin Directory Structure

Every plugin MUST follow this directory layout:

```
src/plugins/<plugin-name>/
  ├── <plugin-name>.plugin.ts       # Plugin definition (or plugin.ts)
  ├── constants.ts                   # Permissions, logger symbols, injection tokens
  ├── entities/
  │   ├── <entity>.entity.ts         # Main entity
  │   └── <entity>-translation.entity.ts  # Only if translatable
  ├── services/
  │   └── <entity>.service.ts        # Business logic
  ├── api/
  │   ├── extension.ts               # GraphQL schema (admin + shop)
  │   ├── admin.resolver.ts          # Admin API resolver
  │   └── shop.resolver.ts           # Shop API resolver (if needed)
  └── types.ts                       # TypeScript type augmentations (if using custom fields)
```

---

## Plugin Definition

```typescript
import { PluginCommonModule, VendurePlugin } from '@vendure/core';

@VendurePlugin({
    imports: [PluginCommonModule],
    entities: [MyEntity, MyEntityTranslation],  // Register ALL entities including translations
    adminApiExtensions: {
        schema: adminApiExtensions,
        resolvers: [MyAdminResolver],
    },
    shopApiExtensions: {
        schema: shopApiExtensions,
        resolvers: [MyShopResolver],
    },
    providers: [MyService],
    configuration: config => {
        config.authOptions.customPermissions.push(myPermission);
        return config;
    },
    compatibility: '^3.0.0',
})
export class MyPlugin {}
```

Rules:
- ALWAYS import `PluginCommonModule`
- ALWAYS set `compatibility: '^3.0.0'`
- Register custom permissions via `configuration` callback pushing to `config.authOptions.customPermissions`
- Register ALL entities including translation entities in the `entities` array
- If the plugin needs configurable options, use the static `init()` pattern:

```typescript
export class MyPlugin {
    static options: MyPluginOptions;
    static init(options: MyPluginOptions): Type<MyPlugin> {
        this.options = options;
        return MyPlugin;
    }
}
```

