## Entity Definitions

### Simple Entity (no translations)

```typescript
import { DeepPartial, VendureEntity, ID } from '@vendure/core';
import { Entity, Column, ManyToOne, Index } from 'typeorm';

@Entity()
export class MyEntity extends VendureEntity {
    constructor(input?: DeepPartial<MyEntity>) {
        super(input);
    }

    @Column()
    name: string;

    @Column({ type: 'boolean', default: true })
    enabled: boolean;
}
```

### Translatable Entity

When an entity has fields that need multi-language support (titles, descriptions, content, slugs, etc.), use the Translatable pattern.

**When to use Translatable:**
- Entity has user-facing text fields (names, titles, descriptions, content, slugs, meta tags)
- Content will be displayed to end customers in their language

**When NOT to use Translatable:**
- Entity only has system fields (status, dates, numeric values, boolean flags, relations)
- Entity stores internal/technical data

**Parent entity:**

```typescript
import { DeepPartial, VendureEntity, Translatable, Translation, LocaleString } from '@vendure/core';
import { Entity, Column, OneToMany, DeleteDateColumn } from 'typeorm';

@Entity()
export class MyEntity extends VendureEntity implements Translatable {
    constructor(input?: DeepPartial<MyEntity>) {
        super(input);
    }

    // Translatable fields - NO @Column decorator, type is LocaleString
    title: LocaleString;
    content: LocaleString;

    // Non-translatable fields - HAVE @Column decorator
    @Column({ type: 'boolean' })
    enabled: boolean;

    @DeleteDateColumn({ nullable: true })
    deletedAt: Date | null;

    // Translations relation - MUST be eager: true
    @OneToMany(type => MyEntityTranslation, t => t.base, { eager: true })
    translations: Array<Translation<MyEntity>>;
}
```

**Translation entity:**

```typescript
import { DeepPartial, VendureEntity, LanguageCode } from '@vendure/core';
import { Translation } from '@vendure/core';
import { Entity, Column, ManyToOne, Index } from 'typeorm';

@Entity()
export class MyEntityTranslation extends VendureEntity implements Translation<MyEntity> {
    constructor(input?: DeepPartial<Translation<MyEntityTranslation>>) {
        super(input);
    }

    @Column('varchar')
    languageCode: LanguageCode;

    // Translatable fields as regular @Column - same names as parent
    @Column()
    title: string;

    @Column({ type: 'text' })
    content: string;

    // Back-reference - MUST use onDelete: 'CASCADE' and @Index
    @Index()
    @ManyToOne(type => MyEntity, base => base.translations, { onDelete: 'CASCADE' })
    base: MyEntity;
}
```

Key rules for Translatable:
- Translatable fields on parent entity: type `LocaleString`, NO `@Column()` decorator
- Same-named fields on translation entity: regular `@Column()` with `string` type
- Translation `@OneToMany` on parent MUST have `{ eager: true }`
- Translation `@ManyToOne` back to parent MUST have `{ onDelete: 'CASCADE' }` and `@Index()`
- Translation relation property MUST be named `base`
- Constructor of translation: `DeepPartial<Translation<MyEntityTranslation>>`

### Channel-Aware Entity

When an entity should be scoped to specific channels (multi-store/multi-tenant), implement `ChannelAware`:

```typescript
import { ChannelAware, Channel } from '@vendure/core';
import { ManyToMany, JoinTable } from 'typeorm';

@Entity()
export class MyEntity extends VendureEntity implements Translatable, ChannelAware {
    // ... other fields

    @ManyToMany(() => Channel)
    @JoinTable()
    channels: Channel[];
}
```

### Soft Deletes

Use `@DeleteDateColumn` for soft deletes:

```typescript
@DeleteDateColumn({ nullable: true })
deletedAt: Date | null;
```

Always filter with `{ deletedAt: IsNull() }` in queries.

