## Resolver Layer

Resolvers MUST be thin pass-throughs that delegate to services. NEVER put business logic in resolvers.

### Admin Resolver

```typescript
import { Args, Mutation, Query, Resolver } from '@nestjs/graphql';
import { Allow, Ctx, RequestContext, Transaction } from '@vendure/core';
import { MutationCreateMyEntityArgs, MutationUpdateMyEntityArgs } from '../../../codegen/adminTypes';

@Resolver()
export class MyAdminResolver {
    constructor(private myService: MyService) {}

    @Allow(myPermission.Read)
    @Query()
    async myEntities(@Ctx() ctx: RequestContext, @Args() args: any) {
        return this.myService.findAll(ctx, args.options);
    }

    @Allow(myPermission.Read)
    @Query()
    async myEntity(@Ctx() ctx: RequestContext, @Args() args: any) {
        return this.myService.findOne(ctx, args.id);
    }

    @Allow(myPermission.Create)
    @Mutation()
    async createMyEntity(@Ctx() ctx: RequestContext, @Args() args: MutationCreateMyEntityArgs) {
        return this.myService.create(ctx, args.input);
    }

    @Allow(myPermission.Update)
    @Mutation()
    async updateMyEntity(@Ctx() ctx: RequestContext, @Args() args: MutationUpdateMyEntityArgs) {
        return this.myService.update(ctx, args.input);
    }

    @Transaction()
    @Allow(myPermission.Delete)
    @Mutation()
    async deleteMyEntity(@Ctx() ctx: RequestContext, @Args() args: any) {
        return this.myService.delete(ctx, args.ids);
    }
}
```

Rules:
- Use `@Allow()` with the correct CRUD permission on every resolver method
- Use `@Transaction()` on delete mutations and any mutation doing multiple DB writes
- Queries do NOT need `@Transaction()`
- Create/Update mutations typically do NOT need `@Transaction()` (TranslatableSaver handles it)
- Import mutation arg types from `../../../codegen/adminTypes` (auto-generated)
- NEVER put try-catch in resolvers

### Shop Resolver

```typescript
@Resolver()
export class MyShopResolver {
    constructor(private myService: MyService) {}

    @Query()
    async myEntities(@Ctx() ctx: RequestContext, @Args() args: any) {
        return this.myService.findAll(ctx, {
            ...args.options,
            filter: { enabled: { eq: true } },  // Force-filter to only show enabled
        });
    }
}
```

Rules:
- Shop resolvers are typically read-only (queries only)
- No `@Allow()` decorator needed for public endpoints
- ALWAYS force-filter to show only `enabled: true` or published status
- Use `@Allow(Permission.Owner)` for customer-specific operations

